=== Insider Tips from a Local

#tip-box[
- *The Kusttram is an attraction in itself.* For a unique coastal experience, buy a day pass for the Coastal Tram and ride it from one end to the other (De Panne to Knokke-Heist). It takes over two hours and shows you the incredible diversity of the seaside towns.
- *Check for local events.* Before you go, do a quick search for `"[City Name] events this weekend"`. You might stumble upon a local market, a festival, or a free concert that will make your trip even more memorable.
- *Don't ignore Wallonia.* While the Flemish cities are more famous, Wallonia has incredible charm. Beyond Dinant, consider visiting Namur for its stunning citadel or Tournai for its massive cathedral.
- *Book international trains in advance.* For trips to Paris, Amsterdam, or Cologne, prices on high-speed trains (Eurostar/Thalys) work like airline tickets—the earlier you book, the cheaper they are.
]

Taking that first step to explore is the hardest part. But once you take one trip, you'll realize how easy and rewarding it is. You'll feel more connected to your new country and be reminded of the incredible adventure you're on. So pick a spot on the map, plan a small trip for this weekend, and go make some memories. Happy travels!

